---
title: `$shield::path()`
description: Generate full path of a shield file from its ID.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Shield::path($input, $fail = false);
~~~

Search for PHP file from current active shield folder based on the given name, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = Shield::path('page');
$test_2 = Shield::path('test');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test_1 = '.\www\lot\shield\document\page.php';
$test_2 = false;
~~~

Search for PHP files from current active folder based on the given _namespace_. Otherwise, return the first available alternate file, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$test = Shield::path('page/about/social');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
// can be
$test = '.\www\lot\shield\document\page.about.social.php';
// or
$test = '.\www\lot\shield\document\page\about\social.php';
// or
$test = '.\www\lot\shield\document\page\about.php';
// or
$test = '.\www\lot\shield\document\page.php';
~~~